medical_history.history_of_present_illness: The patient reported axial back pain present for several months, which she thought was related to a fall. Described as sharp and stabbing with a burning quality, the pain was rated 7 out of 10, greater on the left side and worse while sitting. Some control was achieved with celecoxib.
medical_history.past_medical_history: History of bilateral breast cancer, obesity, sleep apnea, hyperlipidemia, hypertension, osteoporosis, and treated hydatidiform mole.
medical_history.family_history: Family history notable for breast cancer in mother (70 years), sister (57 years), and maternal aunt (65 years). Father had prostate cancer and a stroke.
medical_history.social_history: Worked in healthcare, smoked 1 pack daily for 25 years (quit 15 years prior). Married with one adult daughter.
